comment.narrative:
As part of the project, the following were  achieved: (1) A Masters  degree in Environmental Structures of the National University of Forestry (ESNACIFOR) in agreement with the University of Granada – Spain, incorporated  the management of chemicals in its second semester.

(2) 24 people of the 9 month diploma course of Environmental Management of Chemical Products at UNITEC have graduated (members of the public and private sectors have deep knowledge about ESM of chemicals). 


The project helped develop a strategy to educators at all levels of formal education (from basic and higher level) which includes the definition of an Analytical Plan with a list of topics to include the Environmentally Sound Management of Chemicals (ESM) in different subjects of the education system.


Other initiatives include:

1) Curriculum of the Master Programa of Occupational Health promoted by the Faculty of Medical Sciences CIDSTA-SALTRA-National Autonomous University of Honduras - UNAH  (pending approval of the Council for Higher Education); 


2) Curriculum of the Bachelor career in agricultural and environmental chemistry of the University of Agriculture - UNA (pending of approval of the university);


3) Design Diploma in Industrial Safety focusing on Chemicals Management to be offered by the University of San Pedro Sula - USAP (proposal delivered by the project to USAP); 


4) Technical Curriculum in control and environmental monitoring to be offered by the Technological Institute of Tela - ITT / UNAH (Offering at this time);



5) Document for the mainstreaming of the assignment of environmental management of chemical products in the Curricula of Environmental and Analytical Chemistry carreer (Sula Valley University).

During this reporting period, more than 140 members of the national commission on chemicals management have been trained in the subjects of ecotoxicology, chemical response to emergency situations, strategic planning, management of pesticides and inventory of pesticides. 


In addition, project helped organize and developed training events and workshops with CESCCO to other entities besides the aforementioned commission:  

Induction workshop for Soil Standard Committee (20 participants); Informative workshops of new environmental regulations (120 participants); 

Technical training of municipal solid waste management (40 participants); 

Recycling of materials (15 participants) 

Knowledge Fair on Environmentally Sound Management of Chemicals to students in elementary and middle education and general public schools (115 participants); 

Knowledge Fair on Occupational Health / Environmentally Sound Management of Chemicals to public - basic and general education students (150 participants); 

Environment Outlook report - GEO Honduras (200 participants)

- Ejecución de un proyecto piloto en una comunidad afectada por sequía del municipio de Marcovia, Choluteca, con la participación de mujeres jefas de familia y actividades de fortalecimiento de medios de vidas y acciones de gestión de riesgo climático y adaptación a la variabilidad y cambio climático como la instalación de cosechas de agua, sistema de riego por goteo y la producción de cultivos adaptados a la realidad de la región;

- El enfoque de género en el piloto utilizará herramientas que permiten el análisis diferenciado del enfoque de género de proyectos pasados de PNUD BPPS en Honduras (Ejemplo: Piloto de Recuperación Temprana)

- Desarrollo del diagnóstico con la información existente sobre los recursos hídricos, actores, papeles, progreso, limitantes, gobernanza y necesidades;

-Brindar asistencia para la identificación de los requerimientos técnicos y metodológicos que permitan el análisis de la disponibilidad del recurso hídrico;

- Facilitar la cooperación Sur-Sur para la transferencia de conocimientos técnicos metodológicos del manejo del recurso hídrico;

- Elaboración del documento “Gestión del conocimiento en el recurso hídrico incluyendo los problemas de disponibilidad y los problemas de gobernanza”.
